                        <h3 class="question">
                            <i class="down-arrow"></i>Yoga's a girl thing, right?
                        </h3>
                        <div class="answer">



                            <div class="row nopadding">
                                <div class="col-sm-8 col-xs-12 ">
                                    <p>Traditionally, when yoga was the preserve of Brahmins, it was taught man to boy, or man to man. </p>
                                    <p>It all changed when Sri Tirumalai Krishnamacharya (born 1888), a great reformer and the granddaddy of modern day yoga, agreed to teach Indra Devi. 'The first lady of yoga' taught in China and the Soviet Union before opening her Hollywood studio in 1947. Greta Garbo, Elizabeth Arden and Marilyn Monroe went to her classes and the rest, as they say, is a ratio. A 70:30 ratio to be exact.</p>
                                    <p>Yep, the girls are back in town. But hey guys – come on in – the water's lovely.</p>



